The `Object`(#e7e8ea) class has an `equals()`(#e7e8ea) method. This method only returns `true`(#e7e8ea) if two reference variables are aliases (object1 == object2).

To compare specific attributes of an object, we can override the `equals()`(#e7e8ea) method.

```
public boolean equals(Object other) {
  boolean result;

  if (other == null) {
    result = false;
  }
  else {
    Painter otherPainter = (Painter) other;
    result = xLocation == otherPainter.xLocation;
  }

  return result;
}
```


The `equals()`(#e7e8ea) method should be used when comparing `String`(#e7e8ea) objects.
